00:46:26.240 --> 00:46:32.140
of Posen in 1834 and
1835, catchy title right.

00:46:32.140 --> 00:46:34.570
&gt;&gt; Why would they hide the book?

00:46:34.570 --> 00:46:36.110
&gt;&gt; Edward Luft: Well, before

00:46:36.110 --> 00:46:39.720
that time they weren't
considered citizens.

00:46:39.720 --> 00:46:45.080
Naturalization made them citizens
and gave them certain rights.

00:46:45.080 --> 00:46:50.770 position:56%
But they had to meet certain
criteria in order to be naturalized.

00:46:50.770 --> 00:46:55.740
Basically they had to be what
the Spaniards would have called,

00:46:55.740 --> 00:46:58.710
Hidalgos, sons of somebody.

00:46:58.710 --> 00:47:01.960
In this case mostly
because they had money.

00:47:01.960 --> 00:47:06.710
There were restrictions
on living in Posen,

00:47:06.710 --> 00:47:10.320
on marrying etcetera
unless they were citizens.

00:47:10.320 --> 00:47:16.030
And the government took a
chance, they had no way of knowing

00:47:16.030 --> 00:47:20.540
if the Jews would accept
the idea of this sort

00:47:20.540 --> 00:47:22.090
of second class citizenship.

00:47:22.090 --> 00:47:27.030
And they were very very
relieved when Akiva Eger showed

00:47:27.030 --> 00:47:32.700
up to be naturalized under
his German name, Akiva Eger.

00:47:32.700 --> 00:47:38.450
And he is in the book therefore.

00:47:38.450 --> 00:47:40.510
Professor.

